#Occupation Epidemiology
##Introduction
###Occupational Health Aims
	Establishing the causes and determinants of work-related disease
	Ensuring adequate recognition and quantification of work-related disease
	Determining appropriate occupational exposure limits
	Providing evidence for policy-makers
###Benefits for workers
	Reduction of work-related health risks, e.g., by reducing exposure levels
	Elimination/substitution of hazards
	Prevention
	Compensation (through recognition as an occupational disease)
###Benefits for society
	Reduction of environmental health risks
	Derivation and application of exposure limits
	Reduction of the economic burden of work-related disease
